I don&#x27;t really see how ION tables are an improvement over arrays of arrays, e.g.:<p><pre><code>    {
      &quot;headers&quot;: [ &quot;a&quot;, &quot;b&quot;, &quot;c&quot; ],
      &quot;rows&quot;: [
        [ 1, 2, 3 ],
        [ 4, 5, 6 ],
      ]
    }
</code></pre>
Furthermore, ION appears to require you to know the length of your data up front, whereas you could use CBOR unspecified length arrays to stream data from your database without precalculating the table length.   It seems like quite a niche format, though.  Most data is not truly tabular.<p>Also, in the table it claims &quot;Yes&quot; under support for &quot;Cyclic references&quot;, and yet further down the page:<p>> ION has support for expressing cyclic references between objects. At this point this support is not 100% finalized.<p>So surely this should be &quot;Yes(*)&quot;?
